Interface Func2<Return,Param1,Param2>

  • Type Parameters:
    Return - the return type
    Param1 - the first parameter
    Param2 - the second parameter

    public interface Func2<Return,Param1,Param2>
    The function interface which takes two parameter and returns something. When Func1 is used in a method parameter declaration, you may consider using wildcards:

    <T, U, V> V someMethod(Func2<? extends V, ? super T, ? super U> f);
